#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.38:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.38:0.2"
msgid "4. Nīvaraṇavagga"
msgstr "4. Hindrances"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 38. Āvaraṇanīvaraṇasutta → anīvaraṇasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn46.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Āvaraṇanīvaraṇasutta"
msgstr "38. Obstacles"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.95"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.38:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcime, bhikkhave, āvaraṇā nīvaraṇā cetaso upakkilesā paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are these five obstacles and hindrances, corruptions of "
"the heart that weaken wisdom."

msgctxt "sn46.38:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn46.38:1.3"
msgid ""
"Kāmacchando, bhikkhave, āvaraṇo nīvaraṇo cetaso upakkileso paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇo."
msgstr "Sensual desire,"

msgctxt "sn46.38:1.4"
msgid ""
"Byāpādo, bhikkhave, āvaraṇo nīvaraṇo cetaso upakkileso paññāya dubbalīkaraṇo."
msgstr "ill will,"

msgctxt "sn46.38:1.5"
msgid ""
"Thinamiddhaṃ, bhikkhave, āvaraṇaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ cetaso upakkilesaṃ paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "dullness and drowsiness,"

msgctxt "sn46.38:1.6"
msgid ""
"Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ, bhikkhave, āvaraṇaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ cetaso upakkilesaṃ paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "restlessness and remorse,"

msgctxt "sn46.38:1.7"
msgid ""
"Vicikicchā, bhikkhave, āvaraṇā nīvaraṇā cetaso upakkilesā paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇā."
msgstr "and doubt."

msgctxt "sn46.38:1.8"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca āvaraṇā nīvaraṇā cetaso upakkilesā paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇā."
msgstr ""
"These are the five obstacles and hindrances, corruptions of the heart that "
"weaken wisdom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.38:2.1"
msgid ""
"Sattime, bhikkhave, bojjhaṅgā anāvaraṇā anīvaraṇā cetaso anupakkilesā "
"bhāvitā bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiphalasacchikiriyāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"There are these seven awakening factors that are not obstacles, hindrances, "
"or corruptions of the mind. When developed and cultivated they lead to the "
"realization of the fruit of knowledge and freedom."

msgctxt "sn46.38:2.2"
msgid "Katame satta?"
msgstr "What seven?"

msgctxt "sn46.38:2.3"
msgid ""
"Satisambojjhaṅgo, bhikkhave, anāvaraṇo anīvaraṇo cetaso anupakkileso bhāvito "
"bahulīkato vijjāvimuttiphalasacchikiriyāya saṃvattati … pe … "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo, bhikkhave, anāvaraṇo anīvaraṇo cetaso anupakkileso "
"bhāvito bahulīkato vijjāvimuttiphalasacchikiriyāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"The awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, "
"rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity."

msgctxt "sn46.38:2.4"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā anāvaraṇā anīvaraṇā cetaso anupakkilesā "
"bhāvitā bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiphalasacchikiriyāya saṃvattantīti."
msgstr ""
"These seven awakening factors are not obstacles, hindrances, or corruptions "
"of the mind. When developed and cultivated they lead to the realization of "
"the fruit of knowledge and freedom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.38:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbaṃ "
"cetaso samannāharitvā ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇāti, imassa pañca nīvaraṇā tasmiṃ "
"samaye na honti. Satta bojjhaṅgā tasmiṃ samaye bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"Mendicants, sometimes a mendicant pays heed, pays attention, engages "
"wholeheartedly, and lends an ear to the teaching. At such a time the five "
"hindrances are absent, and the seven awakening factors are developed to "
"perfection."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.38:4.1"
msgid "Katame pañca nīvaraṇā tasmiṃ samaye na honti?"
msgstr "What are the five hindrances that are absent?"

msgctxt "sn46.38:4.2"
msgid ""
"Kāmacchandanīvaraṇaṃ tasmiṃ samaye na hoti, byāpādanīvaraṇaṃ tasmiṃ samaye "
"na hoti, thinamiddhanīvaraṇaṃ tasmiṃ samaye na hoti, "
"uddhaccakukkuccanīvaraṇaṃ tasmiṃ samaye na hoti, vicikicchānīvaraṇaṃ tasmiṃ "
"samaye na hoti."
msgstr ""
"Sensual desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, "
"and doubt."

msgctxt "sn46.38:4.3"
msgid "Imassa pañca nīvaraṇā tasmiṃ samaye na honti."
msgstr "These are the five hindrances that are absent."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.96"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.38:5.1"
msgid "Katame satta bojjhaṅgā tasmiṃ samaye bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti?"
msgstr ""
"And what are the seven awakening factors that are developed to perfection?"

msgctxt "sn46.38:5.2"
msgid ""
"Satisambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati … pe … "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo tasmiṃ samaye bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"The awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, "
"rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity."

msgctxt "sn46.38:5.3"
msgid "Ime satta bojjhaṅgā tasmiṃ samaye bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti."
msgstr "These are the seven awakening factors that are developed to perfection."

msgctxt "sn46.38:5.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbaṃ "
"cetaso samannāharitvā ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇāti, imassa pañca nīvaraṇā tasmiṃ "
"samaye na honti. Ime satta bojjhaṅgā tasmiṃ samaye bhāvanāpāripūriṃ "
"gacchantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Sometimes a mendicant pays heed, pays attention, engages wholeheartedly, and "
"lends an ear to the teaching. At such a time the five hindrances are absent, "
"and the seven awakening factors are developed to perfection.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.38:5.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
